will not affect myjudgement.

48:39.440 --> 48:40.965
If you see any guns,

48:42.080 --> 48:43.844
check the serial numbers
against that list.

48:48.520 --> 48:49.760
Your father...

48:50.240 --> 48:52.971
was the finest officer
I ever worked with.

48:53.960 --> 48:56.247
I know he'd be very, very proud of you.

49:26.240 --> 49:29.403
Danny, as you know,
the man you killed was Italian.

49:31.120 --> 49:34.044
Those two men over there
are his brothers.

49:36.920 --> 49:38.809
If I let the Italians do this, Danny,

49:40.040 --> 49:42.327
they'll cut off your manhood
and let you drain.

49:43.520 --> 49:45.522
That's how those bastards do things.

49:47.560 --> 49:50.564
So, to stop a war breaking out
between us and the Italians,

49:52.880 --> 49:55.008
to save you from their barbarity,

49:58.440 --> 49:59.965
I said I would dispatch you myself.

50:02.920 --> 50:04.365
They're here to witness.

50:12.080 --> 50:14.287
I died over there anyway, Tommy.

50:15.720 --> 50:17.563
I left my fucking brains in the mud.

50:21.800 --> 50:23.689
Do you have any last requests, comrade?

50:29.560 --> 50:33.246
You look out for my Rosie and my boys.

50:35.400 --> 50:36.765
See they get apprenticeships.

50:37.520 --> 50:39.966
At the BSA factory or the Austin.

50:43.320 --> 50:45.368
And they'll make foremen,
I know they will.

50:47.360 --> 50:49.488
Justmordinary.

50:50.560 --> 50:52.164
Just ordinary men.

50:53.040 --> 50:55.008
And they won't get told to do this shit.

50:56.080 --> 50:59.482
This shit...
This shit that we got told to do!

51:01.560 --> 51:03.403
(WHIMPERING)

51:11.920 --> 51:13.843
I suppose I ought to pray now.

51:17.800 --> 51:19.290
Those fucking guns,

51:20.560 --> 51:22.642
they blew God right outta me head.

51:29.080 --> 51:30.764
Is that boat for me?

51:34.760 --> 51:37.001
We have to get your body
out of the city, Danny.

51:37.600 --> 51:38.726
This new copper, you know.

51:39.000 --> 51:41.002
Don't bury me anywhere there's mud.

51:41.480 --> 51:42.481
Okay?

51:43.440 --> 51:44.441
Promise me.

51:47.280 --> 51:49.089
Bury me on a hill,

51:49.360 --> 51:51.249
and tell Rosie where.

51:54.640 --> 51:56.404
You're a good man,

51:57.280 --> 51:59.123
and a good soldier.

52:02.600 --> 52:04.443
Yes, Sergeant Major.

52:26.200 --> 52:27.804
In the bleak mid-winter...

53:17.560 --> 53:19.608
ARTHUR: Where are ya?

53:22.960 --> 53:24.371
It bloody won.

53:24.720 --> 53:27.121
Monaghan Boy bloody won!

53:28.720 --> 53:31.041
Yeah. It won.

53:32.560 --> 53:34.005
And word will spread.

53:34.720 --> 53:36.484
So the next time we do the powder trick,

53:36.560 --> 53:39.689
it won't be just a garrison
that'll bet on the horse.

53:39.760 --> 53:41.569
It'll be the whole of Small Heath.

53:41.640 --> 53:43.165
And you know what?

53:44.040 --> 53:45.804
The horse will win again.

53:45.880 --> 53:49.407
And the third time we do it we'll have
the whole of Birmingham betting on it.

53:49.480 --> 53:52.962
A thousand-quid bet on the magic horse.

53:53.040 --> 53:54.690
And that time...

53:55.400 --> 53:57.209
when we are ready...

53:57.280 --> 53:58.645
the horse will lose.

54:02.760 --> 54:04.285
Think about it.

54:42.800 --> 54:44.404
CHARLIE: You okay, Danny?

54:44.480 --> 54:45.641
I'm still in shock.

54:47.920 --> 54:49.331
Are you sure this isn't heaven?

54:50.240 --> 54:52.129
If it was heaven,
what would I be doing here?

54:55.920 --> 54:57.684
Tommy wanted you to think it was real.

54:58.280 --> 55:00.044
Try and knock some sense into you.

55:01.160 --> 55:03.288
A shell full of sheep brains
hurts pretty bad.

55:03.360 --> 55:04.646
Aye, it was meant to.

55:07.200 --> 55:08.770
So, where are you taking me?

55:08.840 --> 55:10.126
London.

55:10.200 --> 55:11.929
Tommy has a little job for you.

55:12.000 --> 55:14.480
Give you a chance to say thanks.

55:18.400 --> 55:20.209
You're a Peaky Blinder now, Danny.

55:33.800 --> 55:34.926
POLLY: Bad week?

55:37.280 --> 55:38.850
Heard there was no moon last night.

55:39.520 --> 55:43.764
- I checked. Did you do the right thing?
- Yes, I did the right thing.

56:43.840 --> 56:49.927
<i># Take a little walk to the edge of town
and go across the track #</i>
